This module defines functions to create and configure Vue.js applications and components using Js_of_ocaml. It supports operations like mounting components to the DOM, registering plugins, defining component options (data, methods, props, etc.), and setting global configuration. It works primarily with JavaScript object proxies representing Vue components and applications, along with standard JS types like strings, arrays, and callbacks. Concrete use cases include building interactive web UIs by defining reusable components, managing application state through data and watchers, and rendering templates dynamically.
